04/11/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Zivkovic hinted on Monday (3 November) that early elections might take place. "You may all be surprised when parliamentary elections are called: pleasantly surprised, " Zivkovic told parliament.
In other news, Zivkovic has asked Serbian Transportation Minister Marija Raseta-Vukosavljevic to resign amid allegations of abuse of power. She refuses to leave however, saying the public would view it as an admission of guilt. (B92, Tanjug, BBC, Blic - 03/11/03)
